Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Add the curry powder, apple and onion and saute until onion is translucent. Add soup and cream and stir together. Place chicken pieces in a lightly greased 9x13 inch baking dish. Season with salt, pepper and paprika. Pour apple/cream sauce mixture over chicken and bake uncovered in the preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours. Let cool 10 minutes and serve.